INSERT INTO `fbarticle` (`articleid`, `article`, `artilink`, `artiname`, `tag`) VALUES
(39, 'Musabbirul Alam Fahim > ‎Travelers of Bangladesh (ToB)#ourEurotrip Hello everyone. Today I would like to share my Euro trip experience with you. It’s a bit long write-up; however hope it will be helpful if you are planning for a Euro trip.  Visa: Schengen visa is mandatory to travel European countries. Hence me with my wife applied for our visa through French Embassy & got with multiple entries. For Schengen Visa, apply in the countries\' embassy where you plan to stay longest. Embassy fee will be taken at the embassy during the interview for which pre-appointment needs to be taken. Relevant documents like Forwarding letter, Hotel & Travel Ticket booking voucher, Tour itinerary, Bank statement of last 6 months, Solvency Certificate, NOC with leave approval if employed and Travel insurance will be required. Our route: Overall we traveled to 18 cities/towns within 26 days. Paris (France)-Prague (Czech Republic)-Kempten, Munich, Fussen (Germany)-Salzburg (Austria)-Wengen, Lauterbrunnen, Interlaken, Luzern (Switzerland)-Venice, Jesolo, Florence, Tuscan villages, Rome, Amalfi (Italy)-Santorini (Greece) International Flight: Turkish Airlines from Dhaka-Turkey-Paris & Athens-Turkey-Dhaka Travel Details within Europe:   *Dhaka-Paris by Flight (3days)  Places visited: Eiffel Tower, Louvre Museum, Seine river cruise, Notre Dame Cathedral, Sacre-Coeur Basilica, Quartier Montmartre, Pantheon, Latin Quarter, Palace de la Concorde, Arc de Triomphe & Luxembourg Park  *Paris-Prague by Flight (2days) Places visited: Prague Castle, Dancing House, Old Town Square, Wenceslas Square, Charles Bridge, Petrín Hill & Vysehrad Castle  * Prague-Kempten by Bus+Train. Kempten-Salzburg-Munich & Kempten-Fussen day trips by Train (3days) Places visited at Salzburg, Austria: Hohensalzburg Castle, St. Peter’s Abbey, Mirabell Palace, Lovers Bridge, Old Town & Mozart’s Birthplace  Places visited at Munich: Munich Residenz, Marienplatz  Places visited at Fussen: Neuschwanstein Castle, Hohenschwangau Castle  *Kempten-Wengen by Train. Wengen-Lauterbrunnen-Interlaken day trips by Train (3days) Places visited: Jungfraujoch, Murren, Kleine Scheidegg, Mannlichen,  Lauterbrunnen Vally Waterfalls, Staubbach Fall, Harderkulm & Lake Brienz  *Wengen-Luzern by Train (2days) Places visited: Chapel Bridge, Lake Luzern, Old Town, Lion Monument, Town Walls & Towers & Hofkirche *Luzern-Venice by Train. Venice-Murano-Burano-Torcelo-SanMarco by Water Bus. Venice-Florence by Train & Florence-Tuscany day trip by Bus (5days) Places visited at Venice: Saint Mark\'s Basilica, St. Mark\'s Square Grand Canal, Rialto Bridge, Bridge of Sighs Free, Doge\'s Palace, Murano, Burano & Torcello and Jesolo Places visited at Florence: David’s statue, Florence Cathedral, Ponte Vecchio, Basilica of Santa Croce, The view from Piazzale Michelangelo, Paizza Del Duomo, San Marco, Giotto\'s Bell Tower, San Gimignano & Chianti villages  *Venice-Rome by Train. Rome-Naples-Sorrento by Train & Sorrento-Amalfi by Bus (3days) Places visited at Rome: Coloseum, Roman Forum, Palatine Hills, Vatican City, Museum & Sistine Chapel, Trevi Fountain, Spanish Step, Novano Piazza & St. Peter\'s Square *Rome-Santorini by Flight. Santorini-Athens-Dhaka by Flight (3days)  Places visited: Fira, Kamari Beach, Perissa beach, Akrotiri, Imerovigli & Oia  Tips: • Paris & Switzerland were most expensive. Prague was the cheapest among the visited countries. Germany, Italy & Greece were moderately pricey.  • Day\'s length is long in summer (almost 17hrs of day light), so you will get ample time to explore the cities.  • You will need to walk a lot in European Cities, so wear comfortable shoes. • Buy the tickets & book hotel immediately after getting the visa confirmation & plan well before your travel schedule, otherwise cost will increase shortly • Intercity Flight & Train tickets cost increases with time but Bus tickets are nearly same at all times (with some exceptions) • Travel Pass: We bought 7 days pass for Metro at Paris which costs 23 Euro each, bought 24 hrs Tram day Pass at Prague which cost 110 Crown each, 3 days Jungfrau Pass for Berner Oberland region cost 180 Swiss Franc each, 3 days Metro pass at Rome cost 18 Euro each, 1 day Water Bus Pass at Venice cost 20 Euro each. • Uber is available at Paris (not found in other visited cities), but works with Credit Card only. • We bought Lebara Roaming Sim at 10 Euro each, which ran in all EU countries except Switzerland.  • If you are interested to go to Jungfrau region & stay at Bernese Oberland area (Lauterbrunnen/Wengen), then better to buy Jungfrau Pass for 3 days rather buying Swiss pass.  • Euro is well acceptable among all of countries we visited. But found exchange rate quite less in the stores at Switzerland comparing to Swiss Franc. • City Tax will be charged during the check out process from any hotel (in addition to hotel rent). • Better to stay near city center at every city (if you want to utilize your time properly). • For planning of our trip www.goeuro.com, www.rome2rio.com & Google map were the saviors. For accommodation www.booking.com & www.agoda.com helped us a lot.  • Online check in might be mandatory for some budget air at Europe. So please follow the instructions during booking of the tickets.  • Do your own research & prepare plan as early as possible because visa might be confirmed at the very last hour too, so keep time in hand as much as possible.  • To save expense, try to buy the Train tickets via online in advance, since spot purchase will cost high.  For us, it was a trip to cherish for lifetime and totally worthy ???? Total cost of our trip was around 3,800 Euro each. While traveling pls don\'t through waste (plastics bags, bottles) here & there. Plant tree to save environment whereever you visit and if you re-visit there, see your plant growing ???? , and always support tourists in need at home and foreign countries (in all of my visited countries, European people were amazingly hospitable and helpful and we didnt have to bother about taking our own photos, because these people, even office going people, asked us if we needed to take any picture of us)30 August at 14:50 · Public', 'https://mobile.facebook.com/groups/22012931789?view=permalink&id=10155517434096790&refid=18&_ft_=qid.6596692059854373966%3Amf_story_key.10155517434096790%3Atop_level_post_id.10155517434096790%3Atl_objid.10155517434096790%3Asrc.22%3Aphoto_attachments_list.%5B10156118987644006%2C10156118988899006%2C10156118987204006%2C10156119037494006%2C10156118990464006%5D&__tn__=%2As-R', '', ''),
